channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump's Victory May Herald a Fundamental Reordering of American Politics
Fox News projects Democrat Tammy Baldwin survives tight race to hold Wisconsin Senate seat
item.description: The Fox News Decision Desk projects that Tammy Baldwin fended off a competitive challenge for her Senate seat from businessman Eric Hovde.

item.title: Jan. 6 Defendant Denied Case Delay as Trump Pardon Looms
item.description: A federal judge denied a request from a man charged for being at the Jan. 6 unrest at the U.S. Capitol, who argued his case should be delayed because of a possible pardon from President-elect Donald Trump.

item.title: BREAKING: DOJ Set to Drop Cases Against Trump Before Inauguration
GOP challenger unseats Rep. Susan Wild in Pennsylvania
item.description: Pennsylvania Democratic Rep. Susan Wild faced Republican challenger Ryan Mackenzie for the 7th Congressional District seat in the Keystone State.

item.title: RFK Jr. Receives More Than a Half-Million Votes
item.description: Robert F. Kennedy Jr., who appeared on 33 ballots even after dropping his independent bid for the presidency, netted 594,000 votes, about 0.4% of the popular vote total, according to reports Wednesday.

item.title: Pennsylvania Democrat Rep. Matt Cartwright concedes race to GOP challenger
item.description: Democrat Pennsylvania Rep. Matt Cartwright faced Republican challenger, local businessman, Rob Bresnahan in the race for the state's 8th Congressional District seat.

item.title: Jeff Bezos Congratulates Trump on Victory
item.description: Billionaire Jeff Bezos congratulated President-elect Donald Trump on winning the presidential election Wednesday morning, less than two weeks after he prevented The Washington Post from running an endorsement for Democrat presidential candidate Kamala Harris.

item.title: It Begins: DNC Official Tosses Harris and Walz Under the Bus As Intraparty Civil War Looms
California DA Pamela Price recalled over 'progressive leftist' crime policies
item.description: Alameda County residents voted to oust District Attorney Pamela Price on Wednesday. Oakland Mayor Sheng Thao was also ousted from office.

item.title: Burt Jones to Newsmax: Willis Reelection Won't Help Case Against Trump
item.description: Georgia Lieutenant Gov. Burt Jones told Newsmax on Wednesday that it "was not a surprise" that Fani Willis got reelected as Fulton County District Attorney, but said that this won't prevent her case against former President Donald Trump from being thrown out.Jones noted on...

item.title: 'Got our a--es kicked': Dems privately fret about losing House after GOP victory in White House, Senate
item.description: Democrats are growing increasingly concerned that their path to flipping the House of Representatives is narrowing.

item.title: Sen. Cramer to Newsmax: Republicans Obligated to 'Do Big Things'
item.description: Sen. Kevin Cramer, R-S.D., is thrilled to have Republicans again in control of the Senate, he told Newsmax on Wednesday.
